'''''Byron''''' is a historical play by the British writer [[Alicia Ramsey]], which was first performed in 1908. It depicts the life of the early nineteenth century writer [[Lord Byron]].

==Adaptation==
{{Main|A Prince of Lovers}}
In 1922 the play was adapted into a silent film ''[[A Prince of Lovers]]'' directed by [[Charles Calvert (director)|Charles Calvert]] and starring [[Howard Gaye]] as Byron.

