'''Glasgow International (GI)''' is a biennial [[visual arts]] [[arts festival|festival]] that takes place in [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]]. While Glasgow has a thriving contemporary art scene of its own, GI offers a platform to artists from other countries as well,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-glasgow-west-26882625|title=Glasgow International arts festival gets under way|date=4 April 2014|accessdate=4 April 2014|publisher=''BBC News''}}</ref> showcasing the best of both local and international contemporary art.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eveningtimes.co.uk/opinion/columnists/cats-eyes-on-glasgow-mums-the-word.1396001153|title=Cat's Eyes on Glasgow: mum's the word|date=28 March 2014|accessdate=4 April 2014}}</ref> The festival started in 2005<ref>{{cite news|last=Beaton|first=Connor|url=http://thetarge.co.uk/article/culture/0238/glasgow-international-arts-festival-begins|title=Glasgow International arts festival begins|publisher=''The Targe''}}</ref> and the 2014 festival is its sixth edition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theskinny.co.uk/art/previews/own_art/307543-own_art_glasgow_international_2014|title=Own Art: Glasgow International 2014|date=1 April 2014|accessdate=1 April 2014}}</ref>

