{{Expand Spanish|date=May 2011|Mundial (revista)}} '''''Mundial''''' was a [[Peru]]vian weekly [[magazine]]. It was one of the publications that marked the birth of modern journalism in Peru, both for its graphic design and its content when it appeared in Lima on April 28, 1920. It reached up to number 576, corresponding to 4 September 1931. Its director was [[Andrés Avelino Aramburú Salinas]] and it was printed on the site of the “[[La Opinión Nacional]]” on Calle Mantas 152.
